27 def remove_shm_from_resource_tracker():
28  """Monkey-patch multiprocessing.resource_tracker so SharedMemory won't be tracked
29 
30  More details at: https://bugs.python.org/issue38119
31 
32  https://bugs.python.org/issue38119#msg388287

34  #
35  def fix_register(name, rtype):
36  if rtype == "shared_memory":
37  return
38  return resource_tracker._resource_tracker.register(self, name, rtype)
39  resource_tracker.register = fix_register
40  #
41  def fix_unregister(name, rtype):
42  if rtype == "shared_memory":
43  return
44  return resource_tracker._resource_tracker.unregister(self, name, rtype)
45  resource_tracker.unregister = fix_unregister

185  def step(self, action):
186  """
187  Performs one simulation (as defined with episodeType and config params in env.reset()).
188 
189  If action is set to None, a step is performed without changing internal params of the controller.
190  """
191  # An action of none corresponds to changes of 0 for each param
192  if np.any(action == None): action = [ 0 for _ in self.jointParams["Defaults"] ]
193 
194  # If action is not within action space, terminate the episode and return
195  if False in [ -1 <= a <= 1 for a in action ]:
196  return self.formatObs(), -100, True, {}
197 
198  action = self.actionToParams(action)
199 
200  # Limit action to a precision of 3 decimal points
201  action = np.round( np.array(action) , decimals=3)
202 
203  # Calculate current controller params after action
204  self.currentParams += np.array(action)
205 
206  # Clip controller params to Min/Max
207  np.clip(
208  self.currentParams,
209  self.jointParams["Minimums"],
210  self.jointParams["Maximums"],
211  out = self.currentParams
212  )
213 
214  # Deactivate torque control
215  #self.torqueControlUpdate(0)
216  #self.waitForPhysicsUpdate()
217  # Set joint to initial position
218  while abs( self.getJointState()[0] - self.controlSignal[0]) > 0.01:
219  self.positionControlUpdate(cmdForce=100, cmdPos=self.controlSignal[0])
220  self.waitForPhysicsUpdate()
221  # Deactivate position control before proceeding
222  self.positionControlUpdate()
223  self.waitForPhysicsUpdate()
224 
225  # Update controller instance
226  self.controllerInstance.updateConstants(self.currentParams)
227 
228  resultingPos = [] # Variable to track resulting motor position
229  actuatorTorque = [] # Variable to track applied actuator torque
230  feedback = self.getJointState() # Variable to track bullet joint feedback
231 
232  # Track step performance
233  debugPerformance = False
234  tracker = performanceTimer()
235 
236  # Iterate over controlsignal
237  for entry in self.controlSignal:
238  if debugPerformance: tracker.reset()
239 
240  # Calculate output torque and apply it to the joint
241  # Since we only test postion control, the vel and effort commands are set to 0
242  torque = PWM2Torque(
243  self.controllerInstance.update([entry, 0, 0], feedback),
244  maxMotorTorque=self.jointParams["MaxTorque"]
245  )
246 
247  if debugPerformance: tracker.addTimestamp(name="Torque calculated")
248 
249  # Track applied torque
250  actuatorTorque.append(torque)
251 
252  if debugPerformance: tracker.addTimestamp(name="Actuator torque appended")
253 
254  # Perform control update
255  self.torqueControlUpdate(torque)
256 
257  if debugPerformance: tracker.addTimestamp(name="Torque update command sent")
258 
259  # Wait for synchronisation
260  self.waitForPhysicsUpdate()
261 
262  if debugPerformance: tracker.addTimestamp(name="Physics update done")
263 
264  # Get joint feedback & correct torque value (it is not reported by bullet in torque mode)
265  feedback = self.getJointState()
266  feedback[2] = torque
267  # Log feedback for reward calculation
268  resultingPos.append(feedback[0])
269 
270  if debugPerformance:
271  tracker.addTimestamp(name="Step done")
272  tracker.printSummary()
273 
274  # Calculate reward
275  reward = self.compute_reard(resultingPos, self.controlSignal, {})
276 
277  # Keep track of resulting trajectory and applied torque signals
278  self.latestTrajectory = resultingPos
279  self.latestControllerOutput = actuatorTorque
280 
281  # Check if end of episode is reached
282  if self.numSteps < self.maxSteps:
283  self.numSteps += 1
284  done = False
285  else:
286  done = True
287 
288  # Return
289  return self.formatObs(), reward, done, {}

291  def reset(self, episodeType=None, config=None):
292  """
293  Resets environment and returns env observation
294 
295  The control signal for an episode can be set using the episodeType param and configured using config, a dictionary defining the episode configuration.
296  Implemented episode types are 'step' and 'custom'. They are configured using these params in the config dict:
297 
298  step (default):
299  performs a step response from initialPos to stepPos
300  - initialPos [float]: Initial position before step
301  - stepPos [float]: Position after step
302  - samplesPerStep [int]: Number of discrete controller updates per performed step response
303  - maxSteps [int]: Number of performed step responses per episode
304 
305  customSignal:
306  performs a custom response (raw input signal is provided in config)
307  - inSignal [list of floats] Applied control signal for each step
308  - maxSteps [int]: Number of performed step responses per episode
309 
310  square:
311  performs response to a square input signal
312  - lowerSignal: Input signal when wave is low
313  - higherSignal: Input signal when wave is high
314  - pulseLength: Length of each low and high pulse
315  - numPulses: Number of performed pulses
316  - maxSteps [int]: Number of performed step responses per episode
317 
318  generator:
319  performs a custom response generated by the hebi trajectory generator
320  - maxSteps [int]: Number of performed step responses per episode
321  - samplesPerStep [int]: Number of discrete controller updates per performed trajectory
322  - sampleRandom [bool] Determines, whether or not trajectory will be sampled from provided configs
323  - timePosSeries [list] List of dicts describing trajectories [ {"times": [0, 1, 3], "positions": [0, 1, 2]} ]
324 
325  Switching between types of control signals is implemented using a dict and each episodeType is implemented as its own method.
326  In order to use any response other than 'step', the reset method must be called as env.env.reset(episodeType=.., config=..) instead of env.reset() due to how Gym's inheritance is implemented.
327  """
328  # If no epsidoeType and config are provided, use the ones stored as class members
329  if episodeType == None and config == None:
330  episodeType = self.episodeType
331  config = self.episodeConfig
332 
333  def step(self, config):
334  """ Creates and configures step response """
335  # Create step response as a simple list and set number of performed tests per episode
336  lenInitialSignal = 10
337  self.controlSignal = [config["initialPos"] for _ in range(lenInitialSignal) ] + [ config["stepPos"] for _ in range(config["samplesPerStep"]-lenInitialSignal) ]
338  self.maxSteps = config["maxSteps"]
339 
340  def customSignal(self, config):
341  """ Configures custom signal """
342  # Set custom signal and number of performed tests per episode
343  self.controlSignal = config["inSignal"]
344  self.maxSteps = config["maxSteps"]
345 
346  def square(self, config):
347  """ Creates and configures square signal response """
348  # Create single pulse as simple list
349  pulse = [ config["lowerSignal"] for _ in range(config["pulseLength"]) ] + [ config["higherSignal"] for _ in range(config["pulseLength"]) ]
350  # Append single pulse multiple times to pulseSignal in order to create the whole signal
351  pulseSignal = []
352  for _ in range(config["numPulses"]): pulseSignal += pulse
353  # Set signal and number of performed tests per episode
354  self.controlSignal = pulseSignal
355  self.maxSteps = config["maxSteps"]
356 
357  def generator(self, config):
358  """ Creates and configures an input signal based on the hebi trajectory generator """
359  # Create trajectory using hebi utils and store position
360  res = createTrajectory(config, ts=self.ts)
361  self.controlSignal = res[:,0].flatten()
362  self.maxSteps = config["maxSteps"]
363 
364  # Create dict to mimick switch statement between different modes
365  episodeTypes = {
366  "step": step,
367  "customSignal": customSignal,
368  "square": square,
369  "generator": generator
370  }
371 
372  # Instantiate controller with default params
373  self.controllerInstance = copy.deepcopy(self.controllerBlueprint)
374  self.currentParams = np.array(self.jointParams["Defaults"], dtype=np.float64)
375 
376  # Create control signal based on set mode
377  try:
378  episodeTypes[episodeType](self, config)
379  except KeyError:
380  # Handle KeyError by setting up an empty episode
381  self.controlSignal = [0]
382  self.maxSteps = 0
383 
384  # Set perfomed steps for this episode to 0 and return
385  self.numSteps = 0
386 
387  # Perform step to populate features required for obs
388  self.step(None)
389 
390  return self.formatObs()

410  def compute_reard(self, achieved_goal, goal, info):
411  """
412  Computes reward of currently achieved vs. the global goal
413 
414  In this context, the achieved goal is the actual plant position, while the actual goal is to follow the control signal as closely as possible
415 
416  """
417  squaredError = np.square(
418  np.array(achieved_goal) - np.array(goal)
419  )
420  return -1*squaredError.mean()

433  return np.array([
